http://www.cs.indiana.edu/~kinzler/vshnu/

"4.SHELL INTEGRATION

Optionally, your regular shell environment can be enhanced to interact
with vshnu as a sort of supplemental visual mode, communicating any
environment changes to vshnu and directory changes between the two
shells.

See the subdirectory here for your command line shell for further
direction. Currently, only tcsh(1) is available. Contributions of other
shell integrations are very welcome (a bash(1) port should be fairly
easy using $PROMPT_COMMAND like tcsh's precmd alias)."

Who would like to write code to integrate zsh and vshnu together? That
sounds almost killer combination. :-)

